The Roma have overcome the moat and returned to the "street of millionaires"
Some of the West Midlands "wealthiest homeowners are once again at loggerheads with determined gypsies who have overcome a council-dug ditch to reoccupy a field next to their homes.
The Roma parked 20 houses on wheels in a field bordering wealthy Solihull Street, jokingly dubbed "Millionaire's Street."
Bringing horses, babies, and many houses on wheels, they returned after being kicked out as recently as May, and were not deterred by a ditch dug by the municipal authorities to prevent their incursions.
