Cornell-Duranleau, 26, died after suffering multiple stab wounds, according to the documents.
A warning issued by the Chicago Police Department says the body was found on July 27.
The police received a call and arrived at the Grand Plaza apartment complex and found the victim with several wounds on his body.
Cornell-Duranleau was pronounced dead at the scene, officials said, and detectives are now investigating the stabbing death as a homicide, while police are actively searching for two suspects.
Latham has been an associate professor of microbiology and immunology at Northwestern University since 2007.
