Putin says the authorities will not give instructions to Rosneft and Gazprom
Vladimir Putin has stated that the Kremlin and the cabinet should be involved in the issue of gas supplies to the Eastern Petrochemical Company (VNHC), but no one will give instructions to Gazprom, like Rosneft.
This is how Russian President Vladimir Putin responded to Igor Sechin's request to help resolve the differences that arose.
The head of state drew attention to the fact that relations between Rosneft and Gazprom should be resolved exclusively on the basis of market principles.
Earlier, the head of Rosneft, Igor Sechin, told a meeting on the implementation of major investment projects in the Far Eastern Federal District that the absence of an agreement with Gazprom on gas for the VNHK jeopardized the project's implementation period.
Sechin noted that the dialogue with Gazprom on this issue continues.
Gazprom proposes to find gas resources from the Rosneft perimeter, but we do not have such resources, "Sechin added.
Recall that Rosneft asked to be allowed to use gas from Gazprom's Kirinskoye field, located on the Sakhalin shelf, for the Eastern Petrochemical Company.
In June, Gazprom said that negotiations on the issue were continuing and that there were "no hard corners."
Did PSG warn Barcelona about Neymar's move three years ago?
The La Liga side may regret their interest in Marco Verratti
Paris Saint-Germain will not stop chasing Neymar after the club offered £189m for his buy-out clause, but did they warn Barcelona of a world-record raid three years ago?
The sensational offer revived the summer transfer window when the Ligue 1 club were poised to break the world record for transfer costs, more than double the previous mark set by Paul Pogba's return to Manchester United last season for £89m.
When the transition is complete, Neymar will become the most expensive player in the world and the highest-paid professional athlete in the world, with PSG offering him a salary of more than £500,000 a week.
Barcelona are known to be furious at the way the offer was made and the way Neymar has broken his contract, despite a source close to the Catalan club's management insisting the club have always done their best for the player since his move from Santos in 2013.
But was the football world warned of this possibility three years ago by the president of PSG?
When Manchester City expressed an interest in hiring Blaise Matuidi in 2014, Nasser Al-Khelaifi issued a stern warning to any club that wanted to lure one of PSG's best players.
"I am not worried because they know that if they touch one of our players, then we will oppose them, we will make offers to their players," Al-Khelaifi said.
"We respect all clubs.
But if they try to recruit one of our players, there will be consequences. "
Barcelona appear to have crossed that line when the Spanish club expressed an interest in PSG midfielder Marco Verratti earlier this summer.
PSG have made it clear they will not release the Italian national team player on any terms, and now Barcelona are likely to feel the consequences of their offer in the form of the loss of one of their most valuable players, Neymar.
