In Ukraine, it was proposed to send Russians to prison for illegally crossing the border
A draft law has been registered with the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine, according to which criminal penalties for Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border may appear in the republic.
According to RT TV channel, the document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament envisages a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment can be increased to five years.
If the offender is apprehended at the border with a weapon, the period of detention will be increased to eight years.
Earlier, it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians trying to enter Russia outside the established checkpoints.
