In Russia, two new territories of rapid social and economic development will emerge - Abaza and Novotroitsk.
Relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, 4 August.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia have been determined.
The city, which has a population of 15,000 people, will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investment by residents, and a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion roubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will operate in TOP Abaza, for example, includes crop production, animal husbandry, production of food, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the territory's dependence on the town-forming enterprise, Abakansky Mine LLC.
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the establishment of the TOR.
The authorities of Orenburg Oblast did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, an area of leading socio-economic development will also be created.
This will help to diversify the single-industry city's economy, reduce its dependence on the town-forming enterprise of JSC Ural Steel, and create more than 2,300 jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion roubles.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will apply in the new TOR includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of fodder, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk was the first of the monotowns in the Orenburg region to receive the TOR status.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR are: income tax of no more than 5% for the first five years, and no less than 10% for the next five years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, use of the free customs zone regime, preferential access to various infrastructure facilities, and preferential rental rates.
