In Moscow, a policeman shot a man in the leg while defending himself from an attack
A policeman shot a participant in a fight in Moscow in the leg after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On August 3, in the evening, the police department of the OMVD of Russia in the Yakimanka district received a report of a fight on Mytnaya Street, 46.
"The police unit that arrived stopped the offence and separated the participants of the conflict," RIA Novosti reported, with reference to the press service of the Central Board of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the capital.
According to police, when one of the parties to the conflict attacked an MIA officer with a piece of glass, the policeman repeatedly warned the man about the use of weapons and fired a warning shot.
This did not stop the hooligan, after which a law enforcement officer shot the man in the leg.
The injured man needed hospital treatment.
